VwHsGaMxr5","state":"input-available","input":{"result":"I have successfully completed the tasks to understand how `.gitignore` and untracking files work in `jj`:\n\n1. **Created `.gitignore`**: I created a `.gitignore` file at `/home/user/myrepo/.gitignore` containing the `build/` pattern to ignore the build directory.\n2. **Untracked `build/output.bin`**: I then used the `jj file untrack build/output.bin` command to explicitly stop tracking the build artifact from the working-copy commit. Since `jj` requires the file to be ignored by `.gitignore` before it can be untracked, this command succeeded.\n3. **Verified the final state**: Running `jj status` and `jj file list` confirms that only `src/main.py` and `.gitignore` are tracked in the working-copy commit, while `build/output.bin` remains on disk but is no longer tracked.\n\nThe repository is now in the expected state."},"callProviderMetadata":{"google":{"thoughtSignature":""}}}]}
